description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for two Patient Safety Managers to join the Patient Safety Team at Walsall Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will support the Divisional Governance Advisors working with a range of clinicians in the delivery of patient safety and quality improvement interventions, including the delivery of key work streams. This includes facilitating improvement in harm free care and will involve taking the lead on discreet areas of work. Working with staff and teams, together, to achieve safe, effective high quality care. Undertaking root cause analysis and working with clinical staff to learn from excellence in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has recently been awarded outstanding for care by the CQC in their latest inspection and encourages an Appreciative Inquiry approach to patient safety and improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire FarnellAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal visit please contact Claire Farnell via email Claire.farnell@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk or Emily Goss via email on Emily.goss@walsallHealthcare.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
